## Data model — `profiles` (Prisma), not `users`

`auth.users` is owned by Supabase. **Do not** define it in `schema.prisma`.

```prisma
model Profile {
  id                String   @id // same UUID as auth.users.id
  name              String
  email             String   @unique
  role              UserRole @default(counselor)
  active            Boolean  @default(true)
  created_at        DateTime @default(now())

  assigned_students Student[]           @relation("AssignedCounselor")
  sessions          Session[]
  logged_incidents  BehavioralIncident[]
  created_plans     SuccessPlan[]

  @@map("profiles")
}
```

Foreign keys from `Student`, `Session`, etc. reference `profiles.id` (same as Supabase user id).

### Auto-create profile on new Auth user (Supabase SQL)

Run in Supabase SQL editor:

```sql
create or replace function public.handle_new_user()
returns trigger as $$
begin
  insert into public.profiles (id, email, name, role)
  values (
    new.id,
    new.email,
    coalesce(new.raw_user_meta_data->>'name', new.email),
    coalesce(new.raw_user_meta_data->>'role', 'counselor')
  );
  return new;
end;
$$ language plpgsql security definer;

create or replace trigger on_auth_user_created
  after insert on auth.users
  for each row execute procedure public.handle_new_user();
```

