---

## Role hierarchy (unchanged)

| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| `owner` | Full access. All students, all data, all admin functions. |
| `assistant` | Same as owner except limited user management. |
| `counselor` | Assigned students only. Cannot create students; cannot access org analytics. |

`canAccessStudent(userId, role, studentId)` in `lib/permissions.ts` — **same logic**; `userId` is **`profile.id`** (Supabase user id). DB-layer filtering unchanged.

---

## Rate limiting

Rate-limit the **login** route / auth attempts (middleware edge or Upstash / Vercel). **~10 requests per minute per IP**; on limit, **429**, no account enumeration.

---

## Sensitive data & logging (unchanged)

- Never log student PII, session summaries, or auth secrets.
- Never return sensitive fields without verified access (see `api-routes.mdc`).

---

## Build & types

- `typescript.ignoreBuildErrors` stays **false**. Fix type errors; do not suppress.

---

## What never happens

- Never trust `userId` or `role` from the request body — always from **`profile`** after `getUser()` + Prisma.
- Never use the **anon** Supabase client on the server to read/write FERPA tables instead of Prisma.
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` or import admin client in Client Components.
- Never skip **`getUser()` + `profile`** in an API route that mutates or returns student data.
- Never create a route that varies data by client-supplied user id without matching it to the authenticated **`profile.id`**.
